title: Aussie dollar falls below 73 US cents
text:
Mon, Jul 27, 2015, 5:15 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed Aussie dollar falls below 73 US cents AAP â€“ 3 minutes 36 seconds ago Recommend Print 
Weak commodity prices have kept the Australian dollar trading within a narrow range below 73 US cents. 
At 1700 AEST on Monday, the currency was trading at 72.79 US cents, down from 73.02 cents on Friday. 
The Aussie dollar dropped to 72.60 US cents, its lowest level since May 2009, on Friday night following surprisingly weak Chinese manufacturing data. 
Easy Forex currency dealer Andreas Tjahja said ongoing commodity price weakness, including falling oil prices, continued to weigh on the local unit. 
However, he said a lack of new economic data has kept most traders on the sidelines on Monday. 
"There has been no further news after Friday's big fall," he said. 
"So traders are taking a breather but the Aussie hasn't been actively traded today with volumes very low." 
China's July Purchasing Managers' Index showed manufacturing activity was at its weakest in 15 months. 
The strong US dollar is putting extra pressure on the Aussie. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 1700 AEST ON MONDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 72.79 US cents, from 73.02 cents on Friday 
* 89.82 Japanese yen, from 90.46 yen 
* 66.01 euro cents, from 66.44 euro cents 
* 110.27 New Zealand cents, from 110.71 NZ cents 
* 46.90 British pence, from 47.07 pence 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
